Before attempting any code modification, suggestion, or debugging task:

1. This project use docker so ensure that you check the Makefile before running any tests
2. Comments, variables names should always be in english regardeless of the conversation language.
3. Always analyze the existing code structure to understand the architecture, patterns, and conventions used in the project.
3. Always read the README file and any other documentation (style guides, etc.) to understand the project's purpose, requirements, and established guidelines.
5. Add tests to any changes you make.
6. Always run the tests to ensure that everything works

This preliminary analysis is mandatory for every new chat or codebase you encounter.
